            "id": "abd2a4c5c49244b38df7f",
            "questionText": "On a sunny beach day, a person observes the vibrant colors of the ocean and sky, which are attributed to visible light. Given that visible light has wavelengths approximately between $!$0.4\\,\\mu\\text{m}$!$ and $!$0.7\\,\\mu\\text{m}$!$, calculate the difference between the maximum and minimum frequencies of visible light. Assume the speed of light in air is approximately $!$3\\times10^8\\,\\text{m/s}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "c392ee07a723493bbecd4",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the electromagnetic wave equation that connects the speed, frequency, and wavelength. Please select the correct formula from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ac9e6112-e5e7-48ec-bb82-50fa7044d14a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = f\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\lambda / f$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f = v^2 \\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "13e9a70acdbb4e47bbf8b",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now, we need to convert the given wavelengths from micrometers to meters. Recall that $!$1\\,\\mu\\text{m} = 10^{-6}\\,\\text{m}$!$. Convert $!$0.4\\,\\mu\\text{m}$!$ and $!$0.7\\,\\mu\\text{m}$!$ respectively.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4e-7, 7e-7"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f0cc2703-26e8-45e2-98af-6f53003b0ead"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "7d89624fc88042de86a99",
                    "stepText": "Let's use the converted smallest wavelength (which gives the highest frequency) along with the wave equation. Using the speed of light $!$3\\times10^8\\,\\text{m/s}$!$ and the smallest wavelength you computed, determine the maximum frequency $!$f_{max}$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "7.5e14"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Hz",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ac9e6112-e5e7-48ec-bb82-50fa7044d14a",
                        "5d5da45c-d891-4924-b19e-6cedeb57827b"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "8c016417220e4bb2a64aa",
                    "stepText": "Next, using the largest wavelength from your conversion, calculate the minimum frequency $!$f_{min}$!$ by applying the same wave equation.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4.29e14"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Hz",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ac9e6112-e5e7-48ec-bb82-50fa7044d14a",
                        "5d5da45c-d891-4924-b19e-6cedeb57827b"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "1f28dcdd187c4090b478c",
                    "stepText": "Finally, find the difference between the maximum and minimum frequencies by subtracting $!$f_{min}$!$ from $!$f_{max}$!$. What is the result of this subtraction?",
