        {
            "id": "905a3957554844fda41b9",
            "questionText": "An air traffic controller relies on a radar system that emits pulses of microwaves to track aircraft. The system calculates the aircraft's distance based on the time taken for a pulse of microwaves to travel to the aircraft and return. If a pulse of microwaves takes $!$200 \\mu s$!$ to make the round trip, calculate the distance (in meters) of the aircraft from the radar system, given that the speed of light is $!$c = 3 \\times 10^8 \\text{ m/s}$!$.",
